#11913
In the swamp~
The black swamp water is deep and cold. A thicket of brambles blocks the way
north. A deep moaning is heard from somewhere deeper in the swamp. From the
east, you see an ethereal, ghostly form emerge from the mist. It seems to be a
part of the mist, or maybe a product of the mist. The ghost floats slowly over
the water moaning some uncomprehensable jibberish. It hesistates in front of
you and then, it raises a misty finger and points in your direction. The ghost
begins to speak. Yooouuuu mmmuuuusssttt dessstrroy.... Suddenly, the deathly
calm of the swamp is broken as a stiff breeze sweeps through the trees. The
wind rips the misty form into feathery fragments. You hear a faint, muffled
scream, "Nnnooo!!"
~
