In the swamp~
The deep muck of the swamp begins to give way to firmer ground. The ground is
still damp and muddy, but rises to the south and west. The way south is blocked
by a thicket of brambles. North and east, you see a mist shrouded expanse of
watery waste. Dark blighted trees struggle up out of the muck only to face the
parasitic attacks of moss and fungi. A large, squat bullfrog sits on a log here
croaking out a warning to the rest of the swamp about your presence here.
