#11928
in the swamp~
The black water runs deep here. A thicket of bamboo prevents passage further
east. Tall dark water oaks rise eerily from the gloom. Thick vines loop around
the tree trunks snaking their way up into the light. As you look, one of the
vines begins to move! It is a snake! As thick as your waist and at least thirty
feet long, this huge reptile looks to be able to swallow you whole! Good thing
for you, it must have recently taken a meal as it slithers slowly deeper into
the swamp.
