in the swamp~
The black water runs deep here. A thicket of bamboo prevents passage further
east. Tall dark water oaks rise eerily from the gloom. Thick vines loop around
the tree trunks snaking their way up into the light. High up in the branches of
the trees you see a huge spider web. Caught up in the web are birds, some quite
large, and some quite alive. As you watch, a skittering movement catches your
eye. An enormous black spider, easily as big as a large dog, moves out onto the
web and attacks one of the living birds. The bird squawks and flutters in a
desperate attempt to escape, yet it is no use. The spider sinks its fangs into
the bird. The bird flutters, then its movements cease.
