#11933
In the swamp~
The muddy ground is covered with oily puddles of stagnant water. Green, leafy
vines creep along the ground, wrapping themselves around any available surface.
As you stand and watch, one of the leafy tendrils snakes across the muck and
begins to wrap itself around your leg. You easily extract yourself from the
tangle, but as you do so you feel a stinging, burning sensation on your ankle.
You examine the area and find a nasty welt has been burned into your skin.
Perhaps you best avoid this poisonous ivy. 
