#11955
Through the bamboo gate~
You stand at the entrance of a small, poor village. Shabby bamboo huts are
raised high above the swamp on shaky looking platforms. The platforms are also
made of bamboo and vines. The huts are arranged in a rough circle around a
clearing. Far to the north you see one hut that stands out from the rest. It
is much larger and sturdier than the ragged huts that surround it. Two humanoid
creatures work here with bamboo knives cutting the thicket back from the edge
of the village. You imagine that the fight to keep the swamp from retaking the
village area must be a constant and never ending battle. Piles of refuse burn
throwing thick oily smoke into the air.
