#11961
Beneath a large sturdy hut~
This hut is built like no other hut in the small village. Instead of bamboo,
this hut is fashioned from split cedar logs. The logs are notched and wedged
with great precision. Dried mud has been used to chink the cracks in the walls.
The roof of the hut is bamboo, with fresh green fronds plaited skillfully
together to keep out the elements. From the looks of it, the fronds must be
replaced regularly. A thick, sturdy trapdoor has been fashioned to the base of
the platform overhead. A solid looking ladder made from cured cedar leads up
to the trapdoor.
~
